ONE THAT,
 AT FIRST GLANCE,

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:07.000
TIME AND TECHNOLOGY
 SEEM TO HAVE PASSED BY.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:10.000
BUT LAWRENCE IS ACTUALLY
 HOME TO A REVOLUTION

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.000
IN THE TECHNOLOGY

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:14.000
OF THE HUMAN HEART.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.000
YOU SEE, A COALITION
 OF COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:20.000
HAVE COME TOGETHER
 IN A LEADING-EDGE APPROACH

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:22.000
TO HELPING
 TEEN FAMILIES.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:24.000
( siren wailing )

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:29.000
IT ALL STARTS
 WITH SOME SIMPLE TRUTHS.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.000
Millie Robinson:
 ONCE YOU HAVE A CHILD,

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:33.000
THERE'S THIS IDEA
 THAT YOU AUTOMATICALLY
 ARE BLESSED

00:02:33.000 --> 00:02:36.000
WITH ALL THIS PARENTING
 KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS
 AND UNDERSTANDING OF THAT,

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:38.000
AND NONE OF THAT
 IS TRUE.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:40.000
ONCE A 16-YEAR-OLD
HAS A CHILD,

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:43.000
SHE DOESN'T TURN INTO
THE MOTHER OF THE CENTURY.

00:02:43.000 --> 00:02:45.000
WHAT SHE TURNS INTO
IS A TEEN MOM.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:49.000
SHE STILL HAS ALL THOSE
ADOLESCENT CONCERNS AND ALL
THOSE ADOLESCENT NEEDS,

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:52.000
AND NOW WHAT SHE HAS IS
A CHILD IN ADDITION TO THAT.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:55.000
Brazelton:
 EACH TEEN PARENT
 IS UNIQUE,

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:57.000
AND SO ARE HER NEEDS.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:00.000
Sharon Thompson:
 SOME OF THE GIRLS LIVE
 WITH THEIR BOYFRIENDS.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
SOME ARE MARRIED.
 SOME LIVE WITH THEIR FAMILIES.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:05.000
SOME ARE IN
VERY GOOD SITUATIONS.

00:03:05.000 --> 00:03:08.000
SOME ARE IN
NOT SO GOOD SITUATIONS.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
SO WE TRY AND GET TO KNOW
EACH OF THEM

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.000
AND WHAT THEIR ISSUES
OR CONCERNS ARE

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.000
AND WORK OUT A PLAN
TO WORK WITH THEM.

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.000
Brazelton:
 JENNIFER'S STORY IS TYPICAL.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:23.000
Jennifer Gaznek:
 WHEN I WAS 15,
 I GOT PREGNANT WITH HER.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:27.000
YOU KNOW, I WAS 15,
 BUT I KNEW I WAS READY.

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:29.000
HER FATHER AND I
 ARE FRIENDS.

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.000
YOU KNOW, WE GET ALONG,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:33.000
AND CHIARA
VISITS WITH HIM,

00:03:33.000 --> 00:03:37.000
YOU KNOW,
A FEW TIMES A WEEK.

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:39.000
Brazelton:
 JENNIFER'S LUCKY.

00:03:39.000 --> 00:03:42.000
FROM THE BEGINNING,
 SHE'S HAD THE SUPPORT
 OF HER PARENTS,

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
A KEY ELEMENT
 TO MAKING IT WORK.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:47.000
Donna Gaznek:
I FELT THAT SHE WAS
A CHILD HAVING A CHILD,

00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:51.000
BUT I LEFT
THE DECISION UP TO JENNIFER
AND I BASICALLY SAID,

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:54.000
"LISTEN, YOU'RE PREGNANT
WITH THIS BABY,

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:56.000
AND LET'S GO FORWARD."

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:59.000
I DIDN'T WANT HER
TO HAVE THE BABY ABORTED.
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO DO IT,

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:02.000
AND I DIDN'T WANT
HER TO DO ANYTHING
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO DO.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:04.000
I SUPPORTED HER AND SAID,
"WE'LL GET THROUGH IT."

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:07.000
Brazelton:
 MANY GIRLS CAN'T LIVE AT HOME.

00:04:07.000 --> 00:04:09.000
MAYBE IT'S THE COLOR.
YOU WANT PURPLE?

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:12.000
Brazelton:
 ANOTHER COMMUNITY PROGRAM
 ACTUALLY PROVIDES HOUSING,

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:15.000
EITHER IN APARTMENTS
 OR GROUP HOMES.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:18.000
Robinson:
 WE PROVIDE A SAFE
 AND SECURE ENVIRONMENT

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:22.000
FOR THESE GIRLS
WHERE THEY CAN RELAX
AND REALLY LEARN AND GROW

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:26.000
AND NURTURE THEIR CHILDREN
IN A VERY HEALTHY,
SAFE ENVIRONMENT.

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:29.000
Brazelton:
 THE PROGRAM IS MORE THAN
 JUST A PLACE TO STAY.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:33.000
Robinson: A LOT OF
 WHAT WE DO IS HELP GIRLS
 TO FILL OUT APPLICATIONS

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:36.000
AND KNOW THE PROCESS,
 HOW TO ADVOCATE FOR YOURSELF.

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.000
IF YOU GET A PHONE BILL
THAT'S INCORRECT,

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:40.000
HOW DO YOU GO ABOUT
STRAIGHTENING THAT OUT?

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
YOU DON'T JUST NOT PAY
THE BILL BECAUSE YOU'RE MAD
AT THE PHONE COMPANY--

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:46.000
YOU KNOW, THOSE KINDS
 OF THINGS.

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.000
Brazelton:
 WHATEVER THE INDIVIDUAL
 PROGRAM,

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:51.000
THERE ARE COMMON GOALS
 FOR THE TEENS.

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.000
WE STARTED THE PROGRAM
TO SEE THAT THE GIRLS

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.000
COULD GRADUATE
FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

00:04:56.000 --> 00:04:59.000
ALSO, AT THE SAME TIME,
WE TRY AND PREVENT
A SECOND PREGNANCY

00:04:59.000 --> 00:05:02.000
BECAUSE WE FEEL,
WITH ONE CHILD,

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.000
IT'S DIFFICULT
BUT DOABLE.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.000
AND ALTHOUGH
IT'S NOT IMPOSSIBLE

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:08.000
TO BE SUCCESSFUL
WITH TWO CHILDREN,

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:11.000
IT MAKES IT MUCH MORE
DIFFICULT TO DO THAT.

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:13.000
YOU TIRED?

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Thompson:
 WE LOOK AT THE GIRLS
 AND THE CHILDREN

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:18.000
AS HAVING
 TREMENDOUS POTENTIAL,

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:20.000
AND WE WANT
 TO WORK WITH THEM

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:22.000
TO GIVE THEM THE SUPPORT
THAT THEY NEED

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
TO BE SUCCESSFUL
IN WHATEVER THEY CHOOSE.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.000
Brazelton:
 AN IMPORTANT PART
 OF EACH PROGRAM

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.000
IS QUALITY CHILDCARE.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.000
Jennifer:
 I HATE LEAVING HER
 IN THE MORNING

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:34.000
'CAUSE SHE CRIES
 FOR AWHILE.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.000
- CALL IF YOU NEED TO.
- ( Chiara crying )

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:39.000
- CALL ME IF
  THERE'S ANY PROBLEMS.
- I'M SURE SHE'LL BE FINE.

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:41.000
( laughing )

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
Brazelton:
 PARENTING CLASSES
 AND COUNSELING

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:45.000
ARE ALSO CRITICAL.

00:05:45.000 --> 00:05:47.000
Jenny Delbrey:
 THESE GIRLS LEARN PARENTING
 IN MANY DIFFERENT WAYS,

00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:50.000
AND THAT'S WHERE OUR ROLE
IS VERY IMPORTANT,

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.000
ESPECIALLY
THE SCHOOL SYSTEM.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:54.000
OUR SYSTEM, FOR EXAMPLE,
WE MEET WITH THE TEEN PARENTS

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:56.000
ONCE A WEEK AND PROVIDE
PARENTING CLASSES.

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.000
SOMETIMES I HAVE
A CURRICULUM.

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
SOMETIMES MY GROUP TAKES
 A TOTALLY DIFFERENT ROLE
 AND TURN

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:03.000
BECAUSE THEY JUST WANT
 TO SPEAK THEIR MIND.

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.000
...HANDLING ANGER,
AND SO...

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:07.000
Brazelton:
 THESE GIRLS NEED TO FEEL
 THAT THEY CAN SUCCEED.

00:06:07.000 --> 00:06:09.000
SOMETIMES, DURING
GROUP MEETING,

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.000
I USE MY PERSONAL LIFE
AS AN EXAMPLE AND SAY,

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:15.000
"I DO KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE GOING THROUGH
AND I KNOW WHAT YOU'RE FACING

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:17.000
BECAUSE I WAS
A TEEN PARENT."

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:20.000
Brazelton:
 PROVIDING THE SUPPORT
 TEEN PARENTS NEED

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:22.000
SO THEY CAN MAKE IT
 ON THEIR OWN.

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:24.000
...YOU KNOW,
WITH A BOOK...

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:27.000
Brazelton:
 ONE COMMUNITY'S GIFT
 TO ALL OF US.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.000
Delbrey:
 THESE TEENAGERS ARE
 REALLY SUCCESSFUL

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:32.000
AND THEY'RE MAKING IT
 BECAUSE THEY LOVE
 THEIR CHILDREN.

